               <dir-section id="BG.DIR.677" id-root="bg.dir" iso="bg" sect-type="defence" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="DIR-SECTREF" usage="ewyb casee">
                    <heading>Defence</heading>
                    <p id="BG.DIR.678">
          The total strength of the armed forces, as assessed at November 2023, was 36,950, comprising an army of 17,000, an air force of 8,500, a navy of 4,450, and 7,000 centrally controlled staff. In addition, there were 3,000 reserves. Bulgaria became a full member of the 
          <xr pageref="N" ref="NATO.IO">North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO)</xr>
           on 29 March 2004. Compulsory military service was officially ended on 1 December 2007.
        </p>
                    <p>A new NATO battlegroup was established in Kabile, in south-east Bulgaria, in 2022. In October Italy assumed command of the battlegroup, which by November numbered approximately 945 troops.</p>
